== Things you can do ==

* Put some facts about yourself on your [[Special:ActiveUsers|user page]].
* Add links to your projects and games.
* Add links to resources and articles.

== Open issues and projects == 

* Collecting Lisp [[Education]] resources.
* Identifying [[UsefulApplications]] for Lisp game developers.
* Building various [[GameCreationEnvironments]].
* Reproducing and eventually squashing the [[Win64Crashes]] affecting some SBCL/SDL programs.
* Using [http://code.google.com/p/blackthorn-engine/wiki/BlackthornStarterPack Blackthorn Starter Pack].
* Identifying [[NeededDocumentation]].
* Completing the [[ILGE2010|2010 International Lisp Games Expo]] and archiving postmortems and other writeups to this wiki.
* Automating build process and packaging of binaries/libs/assets for all available platforms. See also [[QuickLisp]], [[DistributingGames]].
* Engine and language-agnostic DAM (digital asset management) tools. [[AssetManagement]]
* Working with others to add new platforms. [[PlatformSupport]]

